<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-07-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-07-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="581" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d581">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Mexican Chargé</gloss> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">The
                                        Mexican Embassy</hi><lb/><hi rend="italic">New
                                    York</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-07-06"><hi rend="italic">July 6,
                                1907</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 2.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Honorable Sir</hi>: I have had the honor to receive
                            your note No. 60, of the 2d instant, in which you were pleased to reply
                            to mine of May 9 last, in regard to the claim made on behalf of the
                            steamship <hi rend="italic">Tabasqueño.</hi></p>
                        <p>In reply I beg to inform you that I have already brought the substance of
                            your note to the knowledge of my Government for such action as may be
                            proper.</p>
                        <p>Accept, sir, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">José F. Godoy.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>